Source: Winter of Discontent
Author: PYKE
Vol / Page: 1/xiv/47
Edition: 1889,1974
Quote: A number of small chamois-leather bags, each containing a week's earnings, were placed within a large canvas bag, and this was deposited ..., and very carefully concealed, so that no trace remained on the surface to indicate its whereabouts.
